        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 6:00PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 559 PM CDT, a strong thunderstorm was located 5 miles east of
Wing, or 35 miles northeast of Bismarck, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Wing, Tuttle, and Arena.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
